open-minded 1.

If you describe someone as open-minded , you approve of them because they are willing to listen to and consider other people's ideas and suggestions. 思想开明的 [表赞许] 

例： He was very open-minded about other people's work. 他对其他人的工作成果不抱任何成见。 

2. open-mindedness N-UNCOUNT 思想开明 

例： He was praised for his enthusiasm and his open-mindedness. 他由于为人热情、思想开明受到了赞扬。

</div>

